Purview Catalog Service REST API Document API Reference

Purview Catalog Service is a fully managed cloud service whose users can discover the data sources they need and understand the data sources they find. At the same time, Data Catalog helps organizations get more value from their existing investments. This swagger defines REST API of the Hot Tier of Data Catalog Gen 2.

API Endpoint
https://catalog.purview.azure.com/api
Request Content-Types: application/json
Response Content-Types: application/json
Schemes: https
Version: 2020-12-01-preview

Authentication

azure_auth

Azure Active Directory OAuth2 Flow.

flow
implicit
authorizationUrl
https://login.microsoftonline.com/common/oauth2/authorize
scopes
user_impersonation

impersonate your user account

type
oauth2

EntityREST

EntityREST

POST /atlas/v2/entity

Creates or updates an entity in Atlas. Existing entity is matched using its unique guid if supplied or by its unique attributes eg: qualifiedName. Map and array of collections are not well supported. E.g., array<array >, array<map<string, int>>.

json_AtlasEntityWithExtInfo

Atlas entity with extended information.

Request Example
{
  "entity": {
    "classifications": [
      {
        "entityGuid": "string",
        "entityStatus": "string",
        "propagate": "boolean",
        "removePropagationsOnEntityDelete": "boolean",
        "validityPeriods": [
          {
            "endTime": "string",
            "startTime": "string",
            "timeZone": "string"
          }
        ],
        "source": "string",
        "sourceDetails": "object",
        "attributes": "object",
        "typeName": "string",
        "lastModifiedTS": "string"
      }
    ],
    "createTime": "number",
    "createdBy": "string",
    "guid": "string",
    "homeId": "string",
    "meanings": [
      {
        "confidence": "integer (int32)",
        "createdBy": "string",
        "description": "string",
        "displayText": "string",
        "expression": "string",
        "relationGuid": "string",
        "source": "string",
        "status": "string",
        "steward": "string",
        "termGuid": "string"
      }
    ],
    "provenanceType": "number",
    "proxy": "boolean",
    "relationshipAttributes": "object",
    "status": "string",
    "updateTime": "number",
    "updatedBy": "string",
    "version": "number",
    "source": "string",
    "sourceDetails": "object",
    "contacts": "object",
    "attributes": "object",
    "typeName": "string",
    "lastModifiedTS": "string"
  },
  "referredEntities": "object"
}
200 OK
json_EntityMutationResponse

Created with EntityMutationResponse.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "guidAssignments": "object",
  "mutatedEntities": "object",
  "partialUpdatedEntities": [
    {

          "entityGuid": "string",
          "entityStatus": "string",

          "validityPeriods": [
            {
              "endTime": "string",
              "startTime": "string",

            }

          "source": "string",

      "guid": "string",
      "meaningNames": [
        "string"
      ],
      "meanings": [
        {
          "confidence": "integer (int32)",
          "createdBy": "string",
          "description": "string",
          "displayText": "string",
          "expression": "string",
          "relationGuid": "string",
          "source": "string",

EntityREST

GET /atlas/v2/entity/bulk

Lists entities in bulk identified by its GUIDs.

guid: string[]
in query

An array of GUIDs of entities to create.

Array values passed as multiple parameters: ?guid=aaa&guid=bbb
minExtInfo: boolean false
in query

Whether to return minimal information for referred entities.

ignoreRelationships: boolean false
in query

Whether to ignore relationship attributes.

200 OK
json_AtlasEntitiesWithExtInfo

OK.

404 Not Found

No entity is found.

Response Example (200 OK)

The request to associate a classification to multiple entities.

Request Example
{
  "classification": {
    "entityGuid": "string",
    "entityStatus": "string",
    "propagate": "boolean",
    "removePropagationsOnEntityDelete": "boolean",
    "validityPeriods": [
      {
        "endTime": "string",
        "startTime": "string",
        "timeZone": "string"
      }
    ],
    "source": "string",
    "sourceDetails": "object",
    "attributes": "object",
    "typeName": "string",
    "lastModifiedTS": "string"
  },
  "entityGuids": [
    "string"
  ]
}
204 No Content

No Content.

EntityREST

PUT /atlas/v2/entity/guid/{guid}

Updates entity partially - creates or updates entity attribute identified by its GUID. Supports only primitive attribute type and entity references. It does not support updation of complex types like arrays, and maps. Null updates are not possible.

The value of the attribute.

guid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier of the entity.

name: string
in query

The name of the attribute.

Request Example
"object"
200 OK

EntityREST

GET /atlas/v2/entity/guid/{guid}/classification/{classificationName}

Lists classifications for a given entity represented by a GUID.

guid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier of the entity.

classificationName: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The name of the classification.

200 OK
json_AtlasClassification

The classification for the given entity GUID.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "entityGuid": "string",
  "entityStatus": "string",
  "propagate": "boolean",
  "removePropagationsOnEntityDelete": "boolean",
  "validityPeriods": [
    {
      "endTime": "string",
      "startTime": "string",
      "timeZone": "string"

Updates entity partially - Allows a subset of attributes to be updated on an entity which is identified by its type and unique attribute eg: Referenceable.qualifiedName. Null updates are not possible. In addition to the typeName path parameter, attribute key-value pair(s) can be provided in the following format: attr: = . NOTE: The attrName and attrValue should be unique across entities, eg. qualifiedName. The REST request would look something like this: PUT /v2/entity/uniqueAttribute/type/aType?attr:aTypeAttribute=someValue.

EntityREST

GET /atlas/v2/entity/bulk/uniqueAttribute/type/{typeName}

Bulk API to retrieve list of entities identified by its unique attributes.

In addition to the typeName path parameter, attribute key-value pair(s) can be provided in the following format

typeName= &attr_1: = &attr_2: = &attr_3: =

NOTE: The attrName should be an unique attribute for the given entity-type

The REST request would look something like this

GET /v2/entity/bulk/uniqueAttribute/type/hive_db?attr_0:qualifiedName=db1@cl1&attr_2:qualifiedName=db2@cl1

typeName: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The name of the type.

minExtInfo: boolean false
in query

Whether to return minimal information for referred entities.

ignoreRelationships: boolean false
in query

Whether to ignore relationship attributes.

attr_N:qualifiedName: string
in query

Qualified name of an entity. E.g. to find 2 entities you can set attrs_0:qualifiedName=db1@cl1&attrs_2:qualifiedName=db2@cl1

200 OK
json_AtlasEntitiesWithExtInfo

OK.

GlossaryREST

GET /atlas/v2/glossary/category/{categoryGuid}/related

Gets all related categories (parent and children). Limit, offset, and sort parameters are currently not being enabled and won't work even they are passed.

categoryGuid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier of the category.

limit: integer (int32)
in query

The page size - by default there is no paging.

offset: integer (int32)
in query

The offset for pagination purpose.

sort: string ASC
in query

The sort order, ASC (default) or DESC.

200 OK

OK. Gets an array of related categories.

type
object
Response Example (200 OK) 
"object"

GlossaryREST

GET /atlas/v2/glossary/terms/{termGuid}/assignedEntities

Gets all related objects assigned with the specified term.

termGuid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier for glossary term.

limit: integer (int32)
in query

The page size - by default there is no paging.

offset: integer (int32)
in query

The offset for pagination purpose.

sort: string ASC
in query

The sort order, ASC (default) or DESC.

200 OK
json_AtlasRelatedObjectId

OK. An array of related objects (if any) for the given glossary or an empty list.

type
json_AtlasRelatedObjectId
404 Not Found

If glossary term GUID is invalid.

Response Example (200 OK) 
[
  {
    "displayText": "string",
    "entityStatus": "string",

      "lastModifiedTS": "string"
    },
    "relationshipGuid": "string",
    "relationshipStatus": "string",

    "typeName": "string",
    "uniqueAttributes": "object"
  }
]

LineageREST

GET /atlas/v2/lineage/{guid}

Gets lineage info about the specified entity by GUID.

guid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier of the entity.

depth: integer (int32) 3
in query

The number of hops for lineage.

width: integer (int32) 10
in query

The number of max expanding width in lineage.

direction: string BOTH, INPUT, OUTPUT
in query

The direction of the lineage, which could be INPUT, OUTPUT or BOTH.

includeParent: boolean
in query

True to include the parent chain in the response.

getDerivedLineage: boolean
in query

True to include derived lineage in the response

200 OK
json_AtlasLineageInfo

OK. If Lineage exists for the given entity.

400 Bad Request

Bad query parameters.

404 Not Found

If no lineage is found for the given entity.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "baseEntityGuid": "string",
  "guidEntityMap": "object",
  "widthCounts": "object",
  "lineageDepth": "integer (int32)",
  "lineageWidth": "integer (int32)",
  "includeParent": "boolean",
  "childrenCount": "integer (int32)",
  "lineageDirection": "string",
  "parentRelations": [
    {
      "childEntityId": "string",
      "relationshipId": "string",
      "parentEntityId": "string"
    }
  ],
  "relations": [
    {
      "fromEntityId": "string",
      "relationshipId": "string",
      "toEntityId": "string"
    }
  ]
}

guid: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The globally unique identifier of the entity.

direction: string BOTH, INPUT, OUTPUT
in query

The direction of the lineage, which could be INPUT, OUTPUT or BOTH.

getDerivedLineage: boolean
in query

True to include derived lineage in the response

offset: integer (int32)
in query

The offset for pagination purpose.

limit: integer (int32)
in query

The page size - by default there is no paging.

200 OK
json_AtlasLineageInfo

OK. If Lineage exists for the given entity.

400 Bad Request

Bad query parameters.

404 Not Found

If no lineage is found for the given entity.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "baseEntityGuid": "string",
  "guidEntityMap": "object",
  "widthCounts": "object",
  "lineageDepth": "integer (int32)",
  "lineageWidth": "integer (int32)",
  "includeParent": "boolean",
  "childrenCount": "integer (int32)",
  "lineageDirection": "string",
  "parentRelations": [
    {
      "childEntityId": "string",
      "relationshipId": "string",
      "parentEntityId": "string"
    }
  ],
  "relations": [
    {
      "fromEntityId": "string",
      "relationshipId": "string",
      "toEntityId": "string"
    }
  ]
}

TypesREST

Delete API for type identified by its name.

DELETE /atlas/v2/types/typedef/name/{name}

Delete API for type identified by its name.

name: string (1 to 4096 chars)
in path

The name of the type.

204 No Content

On successful deletion of the requested type definitions

400 Bad Request

On validation failure for any type definitions

TypesREST

GET /atlas/v2/types/typedefs

Gets all type definitions in Atlas in bulk.

includeTermTemplate: boolean false
in query

Whether include termtemplatedef when return all typedefs. This is always true when search filter type=term_template

type: string enum, entity, classification, relationship, struct, term_template false
in query

Typedef name as search filter when get typedefs.

200 OK
json_AtlasTypesDef

OK. AtlasTypesDef with type definitions matching the search criteria or else returns empty list of type definitions.

TypesREST

POST /atlas/v2/types/typedefs

Creates all atlas type definitions in bulk, only new definitions will be created. Any changes to the existing definitions will be discarded.

json_AtlasTypesDef

A composite wrapper object with corresponding lists of the type definition.

200 OK
json_AtlasTypesDef

OK. On successful update of requested type definitions.

400 Bad Request

On validation failure for any type definitions.

TypesREST

PUT /atlas/v2/types/typedefs

Updates all types in bulk, changes detected in the type definitions would be persisted.

json_AtlasTypesDef

A composite object that captures all type definition changes.

200 OK
json_AtlasTypesDef

OK. On successful update of requested type definitions.

400 Bad Request

On validation failure for any type definitions.

204 No Content

OK. On successful deletion of the requested type definitions.

400 Bad Request

On validation failure for any type definitions.

TypesREST

GET /atlas/v2/types/typedefs/headers

Lists all type definitions returned as a list of minimal information header.

includeTermTemplate: boolean false
in query

Whether include termtemplatedef when return all typedefs. This is always true when search filter type=term_template

type: string enum, entity, classification, relationship, struct, term_template false
in query

Typedef name as search filter when get typedefs.

200 OK
json_AtlasTypeDefHeader

An array of AtlasTypeDefHeader matching the search criteria or an empty list if no match.

type
json_AtlasTypeDefHeader
Response Example (200 OK) 
[
  {
    "category": "string",
    "guid": "string",
    "name": "string"
  }
]
TypesREST

GET /atlas/v2/types/statistics

Gets type statistics.

200 OK
json_TypeStatistics

OK. On successful retrieve types and corresponding statistics.

Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "typeStatistics": "object"
}

Schema Definitions

json_AtlasAttributeDef: object

class that captures details of a struct-attribute.

cardinality: json_Cardinality
constraints: json_AtlasConstraintDef

An array of constraints.

json_AtlasConstraintDef
defaultValue: string

The default value of the attribute.

description: string

The description of the attribute.

includeInNotification: boolean

Determines if it is included in notification.

isIndexable: boolean

Determines if it is indexable.

isOptional: boolean

Determines if it is optional.

isUnique: boolean

Determines if it unique.

name: string

The name of the attribute.

options: object

The options for the attribute.

typeName: string

The name of the type.

valuesMaxCount: integer (int32)

The maximum count of the values.

valuesMinCount: integer (int32)

The minimum count of the values.

Example
{
  "cardinality": "string",
  "constraints": [
    {
      "params": "object",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "defaultValue": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "includeInNotification": "boolean",
  "isIndexable": "boolean",
  "isOptional": "boolean",
  "isUnique": "boolean",
  "name": "string",
  "options": "object",
  "typeName": "string",
  "valuesMaxCount": "integer (int32)",
  "valuesMinCount": "integer (int32)"
}

json_AtlasBaseModelObject: object

The base model object.

guid: string

The GUID of the object.

Example
{
  "guid": "string"
}

json_AtlasBaseTypeDef: object

Base class that captures common-attributes for all Atlas types.

category: json_TypeCategory
createTime: number

The created time of the record.

createdBy: string

The user who created the record.

dateFormatter: json_DateFormat
description: string

The description of the type definition.

guid: string

The GUID of the type definition.

name: string

The name of the type definition.

options: object

The options for the type definition.

serviceType: string

The service type.

typeVersion: string

The version of the type.

updateTime: number

The update time of the record.

updatedBy: string

The user who updated the record.

version: number

The version of the record.

json_AtlasClassificationDef:

class that captures details of a classification-type.

    json_AtlasStructDef
entityTypes: string[]

Specifying a list of entityType names in the classificationDef, ensures that classifications can only be applied to those entityTypes.

  • Any subtypes of the entity types inherit the restriction
  • Any classificationDef subtypes inherit the parents entityTypes restrictions
  • Any classificationDef subtypes can further restrict the parents entityTypes restrictions by specifying a subset of the entityTypes
  • An empty entityTypes list when there are no parent restrictions means there are no restrictions
  • An empty entityTypes list when there are parent restrictions means that the subtype picks up the parents restrictions
  • If a list of entityTypes are supplied, where one inherits from another, this will be rejected. This should encourage cleaner classificationsDefs
string
subTypes: string[]

An array of sub types.

string
superTypes: string[]

An array of super types.

string
Example

  "entityTypes": [
    "string"

json_AtlasRelationshipDef:

AtlasRelationshipDef is a TypeDef that defines a relationship.

As with other typeDefs the AtlasRelationshipDef has a name. Once created the RelationshipDef has a guid. The name and the guid are the 2 ways that the RelationshipDef is identified.

RelationshipDefs have 2 ends, each of which specify cardinality, an EntityDef type name and name and optionally whether the end is a container.

RelationshipDefs can have AttributeDefs - though only primitive types are allowed.
RelationshipDefs have a relationshipCategory specifying the UML type of relationship required
RelationshipDefs also have a PropogateTag - indicating which way tags could flow over the relationships.

The way EntityDefs and RelationshipDefs are intended to be used is that EntityDefs will define AttributeDefs these AttributeDefs will not specify an EntityDef type name as their types.

RelationshipDefs introduce new atributes to the entity instances. For example

EntityDef A might have attributes attr1,attr2,attr3
EntityDef B might have attributes attr4,attr5,attr6
RelationshipDef AtoB might define 2 ends 

                           end1:  type A, name attr7
                           end2:  type B, name attr8

When an instance of EntityDef A is created, it will have attributes attr1,attr2,attr3,attr7
When an instance of EntityDef B is created, it will have attributes attr4,attr5,attr6,attr8

In this way relationshipDefs can be authored separately from entityDefs and can inject relationship attributes into the entity instances

    json_AtlasStructDef
endDef1: json_AtlasRelationshipEndDef
endDef2: json_AtlasRelationshipEndDef
propagateTags: json_PropagateTags
relationshipCategory: json_RelationshipCategory
relationshipLabel: string

The label of the relationship.

Example

json_PropagateTags: string

PropagateTags indicates whether tags should propagate across the relationship instance.

Tags can propagate:

NONE - not at all
ONE_TO_TWO - from end 1 to 2
TWO_TO_ONE - from end 2 to 1
BOTH - both ways

Care needs to be taken when specifying. The use cases we are aware of where this flag is useful:

- propagating confidentiality classifications from a table to columns - ONE_TO_TWO could be used here
- propagating classifications around Glossary synonyms - BOTH could be used here.

There is an expectation that further enhancements will allow more granular control of tag propagation and will address how to resolve conflicts.

string NONE, ONE_TO_TWO, TWO_TO_ONE, BOTH

json_Relation: string

The enum of relations.

string SEE_ALSO, SYNONYMS, ANTONYMS, PREFERRED_TO_TERMS, PREFERRED_TERMS, REPLACEMENT_TERMS, REPLACED_BY, TRANSLATION_TERMS, TRANSLATED_TERMS, ISA, CLASSIFIES, VALID_VALUES, VALID_VALUES_FOR

json_RelationshipCategory: string

The Relationship category determines the style of relationship around containment and lifecycle. UML terminology is used for the values.

ASSOCIATION is a relationship with no containment.
COMPOSITION and AGGREGATION are containment relationships.

The difference being in the lifecycles of the container and its children. In the COMPOSITION case, the children cannot exist without the container. For AGGREGATION, the life cycles of the container and children are totally independant.

string ASSOCIATION, AGGREGATION, COMPOSITION

string UP, DOWN, CEILING, FLOOR, HALF_UP, HALF_DOWN, HALF_EVEN, UNNECESSARY

json_SearchResultValue: object

The value item of the search result.

@search.score: number (float)

The search score calculated by the search engine. The results are ordered by search score by default.

@search.highlights: json_SearchHighlights
@search.text: string

The target text that contains the keyword as prefix. The keyword is wrapped with emphasis mark.

description: string

The description of the record.

id: string

The GUID of the record.

name: string

The name of the record.

owner: string

The owner of the record. This is an Atlas native attribute.

qualifiedName: string

The qualified name of the record.

entityType: string

The type name of the record.

classification: string[]

The classifications of the record.

string
label: string[]

The labels of the record.

string
term: json_termSearchResultValue

The terms assigned to the record.

json_termSearchResultValue
contact: json_contactSearchResultValue

The contacts of the record.

json_contactSearchResultValue
assetType: string[]

The asset types of the record.

string
Example
{
  "@search.score": "number (float)",
  "@search.highlights": {
    "id": [
      "string"
    ],
    "qualifiedName": [
      "string"
    ],
    "name": [
      "string"
    ],
    "description": [
      "string"
    ],
    "entityType": [
      "string"
    ]
  },
  "@search.text": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "id": "string",
  "name": "string",
  "owner": "string",
  "qualifiedName": "string",
  "entityType": "string",
  "classification": [
    "string"
  ],
  "label": [
    "string"
  ],
  "term": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "glossaryName": "string"
    }
  ],
  "contact": [
    {
      "id": "string",
      "info": "string",
      "contactType": "string"
    }
  ],
  "assetType": [
    "string"
  ]
}

A highlight list that consists of index fields id ,qualifiedName, name, description, entityType. When the keyword appears in those fields, the value of the field, attached with emphasis mark, is returned as an element of @search.highlights.

id: string[]
string
qualifiedName: string[]
string
name: string[]
string
description: string[]
string
entityType: string[]
string

json_SearchRequest: object

The search query of advanced search request.

keywords: string

The keywords applied to all searchable fields.

offset: integer (int32)

The offset. The default value is 0.

limit: integer (int32)

The limit of the number of the search result. default value is 50; maximum value is 1000.

filter: object

The filter for the search. See examples for the usage of supported filters.

Example
{
  "keywords": "string",
  "offset": "integer (int32)",
  "limit": "integer (int32)",
  "filter": "object"
}

json_SuggestRequest: object

The query of suggest request.

keywords: string

The keywords applied to all fields that support suggest operation. It must be at least 1 character, and no more than 100 characters. In the index schema we defined a default suggester which lists all the supported fields and specifies a search mode.

limit: integer (int32)

The number of suggestions we hope to return. The default value is 5. The value must be a number between 1 and 100.

filter: object

The filter for the search.

Example
{
  "keywords": "string",
  "limit": "integer (int32)",
  "filter": "object"
}

json_HookNotificationType: string

Enum of hook notification type. Different behavior will be invoked by the value.

string TYPE_CREATE, TYPE_UPDATE, ENTITY_CREATE, ENTITY_PARTIAL_UPDATE, ENTITY_FULL_UPDATE, ENTITY_DELETE, ENTITY_CREATE_V2, ENTITY_PARTIAL_UPDATE_V2, ENTITY_FULL_UPDATE_V2, ENTITY_DELETE_V2

  "user": "string"
}

The maximum of rows.

The sorted by field.

The start index of the search.
